🚀 Day 1: CRM Basics & Salesforce Fundamentals
🔗 1. What is CRM?

CRM stands for Customer Relationship Management.
It is a technology that helps businesses manage customer information, communication, sales, and services in one platform.

CRM helps companies:

Manage customer relationships
Track leads and sales opportunities
Improve customer support
Organize business workflows
Increase productivity and efficiency
☁️ 2. Why Companies Use Salesforce

Companies use Salesforce
 because:

It is a cloud-based CRM platform
Helps businesses manage customers and sales
Provides automation for business workflows
Allows access from anywhere using the internet
Improves communication between teams
Helps companies track leads, contacts, and opportunities
Supports application development on the Salesforce Platform
📘 3. Key Salesforce Terms Explained
Term	Definition	Meaning
Account	Represents a company or organization	The business/customer
Contact	Represents a person associated with an account	Individual person
Lead	A person interested in a product/service	Potential customer
Opportunity	A possible business deal or sale	Potential revenue
🏥 4. Real-World Mapping
Chosen Scenario: Hospital Management System
Salesforce Concept	Real-World Mapping
Account	Hospital
Contact	Doctor / Patient
Lead	New patient inquiry
Opportunity	Appointment or treatment booking
🔄 5. Business Flow: Lead → Contact → Opportunity → Customer
In My Own Words:
A person first shows interest in a service and becomes a Lead
After collecting details, the lead becomes a Contact
A possible business deal or service process becomes an Opportunity
After successful completion, the person becomes a Customer
🎯 6. What is Trailhead?

Trailhead is Salesforce’s official learning platform that provides:

Interactive learning modules
Hands-on challenges
Practice environments called Playgrounds
Badges and achievements
Step-by-step Salesforce training
👨‍💻 7. What Does a Salesforce Developer Do?

A Salesforce Developer:

Builds applications on the Salesforce Platform
Uses Apex, Lightning Web Components, and APIs
Automates business processes
Customizes Salesforce solutions
Solves real-world business problems
